{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb956d343-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3","identifier":"/us/usc/t39/s1202"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1202"},"text":"§ 1202.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Bargaining units","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The National Labor Relations Board shall decide in each case the unit appropriate for collective bargaining in the Postal Service. The National Labor Relations Board shall not include in any bargaining unit—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb956d344-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3","identifier":"/us/usc/t39/s1202/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any management official or supervisor;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb956d345-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3","identifier":"/us/usc/t39/s1202/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any employee engaged in personnel work in other than a purely nonconfidential clerical capacity;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb956d346-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3","identifier":"/us/usc/t39/s1202/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" both professional employees and employees who are not professional employees unless a majority of such professional employees vote for inclusion in such unit; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb956d347-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3","identifier":"/us/usc/t39/s1202/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" together with other employees, any individual employed as a security guard to enforce against employees and other persons, rules to protect property of the Postal Service or to protect the safety of property, mail, or persons on the premises of the Postal Service; but no labor organization shall be certified as the representative of employees in a bargaining unit of security guards if such organization admits to membership, or is affiliated directly or indirectly with an organization which admits to membership, employees other than guards.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb956d348-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–375","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-08-12"},"text":"Aug. 12, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/733"},"text":"84 Stat. 733","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb956d349-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb956d34a-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb956d34b-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1971","children":[],"tail":", pursuant to Resolution No. 71–9 of the Board of Governors. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/375/s15/a"},"text":"section 15(a) of Pub. L. 91–375","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t39/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
